#umask removes permissions from newly created files and directoies.It defines which permissions are not granted by default.

# file permissions = 666 - umask
# dir permissions  = 777 - umask
  
#Example
  
#  umask 077
  
#  - Owner gets full (7 - 0 = 7)
#  - Group gets nothing (7 - 7 = 0)
#  - World gets nothing (7 - 7 = 0)
  
#  New files → 600, new directories → 700.
#  Running umask 077 applies to:
  
#  - The current shell and any child processes it spawns
#  - All new files/directories created in that session, regardless of location
  
#  It does not: 
#  - Affect other users or other terminal sessions
#  - Persist after you close the terminal
#  - Change permissions on existing files


